  <!-- Home -->
  <div id="home" class="container section">
    <div class="image"><%= image_tag("logo.png") %></div>
    <p>This is the home for our Open Food Data movement. We are working towards an open standard for food information online. 

    <p>The people involved in this are from all over the world, and believe that while there is an explosion
     in the number of services created to help people make better choices about how we produce, consume, 
     and interact with food, the accuracy and completeness of data create challenges that hamper the rate of innovation. </p>

    <p>By sharing information about and making it easier to communicate about food in our food systems, 
    we hope to enable the many organizations and communities working to improve how we eat and solve these challenges.</p>

    <h3>Open Food Data Standard</h3>
    <p>The open food data standard aims to be participatory, and to promote a better food system by 
    supporting information sharing to enhance the work of the many people who strive to improve access to 
    healthy local food, promote small farms and food businesses, and many other critical features of a healthy food system.</p>
  </div>


